node.text: @quiet_indian_wrestler Liberals
Stay at home moms or dads shouldn’t receive a salary unless they do a job from home

What do you think? Should we pay stay at home mom's? Or are there other jobs they could do from home to make money? Comment below and vote on our story🇺🇸
--------------------------------------------------------
#2ndamendment #freespeech #maga #republicans #trumprepublicans #immigration #immigrationreform #buildthewall #trump2020 #mikepence
#liberal #liberalmind #feminism #prochoice #obamacare #healthcare #socialism #occasiocortez #obama #metoo
#impeachment #gop #libertariansfortrump #libertarians #imwithher #believewomen #millenialsfortrump #hillaryclinton #Strongertogether #randpaul
Why should they get paid for taking care of their family? What comes after their work is the reward, which is well earned
Stay at home moms bitch about how hard it is in public. Get a group of stay at home moms together and they will talk like it’s a party.

Then what about paying the Dad...... for fixing plumbing, mowing grass, fixing a leaky toilet, moving the heavy furniture, providing a second car, paying tuitions, books, clothing for the family, buying food, paying utility bills, etc.  He does those things IN ADDITION to working!
It’s called being a parent
What about stay at home dads? They do exist. And where is this funding coming from? Not my taxes.
No because there's Allot more mothers that don't do shit so they'd get paid for nothing
From who?  And heck no. Play dates and pb&j are not the same stress as careers.

No. It’s the working mothers/fathers that have it hard. They worked all day and come home and still need to help with homework, make dinner, clean the house, bath time etc.  Working parents have the stress of a career and doing all the things a stay at home parent does on top of that.

What nominal economic value is added from being a stay at home mom/dad? I believe this would encourage more welfare leeching and the incentive to have more kids to collect a baseless salary where the value of being a SAH parent is very subjective.
@cjskiiiii check mate😂
I identify as a stay at home mom
A salary from whom? Who would pay it? Whos the boss? So many questions.

You make a choice when you become a SAHM. Career or family, you choose family. The reason you get paid as an employee is because you are doing work that is valuable for somebody who is able to pay you. This is not the case for SAHM's, therefore they shouldn't get paid. If there is a SAHM, it should be because their spouse is able to support that lifestyle.
Lol!! They do get paid, roof, food? If you don’t want children, don’t have them
My girl gon get what I give her $
Salary from what
That’s interesting I’ve never even seen this asked or brought up before
No. I was a stay at home mom for a long time. That’s a choice you make to stay home and raise your children. You shouldn’t be paid to raise your children and keep up with your houses
@trap_daddy_ethan the big communist government ofcourse
@truthwingism fuck that
@trap_daddy_ethan I agree fuck that but you wont do anything to stop it
Should who pay them ?
No

First off how would we go about paying them? Tax dollars? Why is it the majority's responsibility to take care of another individual's decision in life?  Society is a made-up construct, the only thing that is real is the individual and their family.
And congratulations we no longer have any women in the work force
@na_narocks34  LOVE*^^
Wtf! NO IT IS CALLED A LABOR OF LIVE FOR A READON ! Can’t handle it then don’t have kids !
@quiet_indian_wrestler Liberals
Who is supposed to pay them? Where does the money come from exactly
Stay at home moms or dads shouldn’t receive a salary unless they do a job from home
